Decide which ONE category best describes this message:

- noise — unsolicited bulk marketing, list-style cold outreach, generic
  newsletters not opted into, automated digest mailers, alert noise
  from already-snoozed monitors. Did not pick the recipient
  specifically.
- transactional — receipts, shipping notices, appointment confirmations,
  2FA codes, password resets, calendar invites, statements, invoices,
  or any machine-generated acknowledgement of an action the recipient
  initiated.
- personal — messages from friends, family, or known acquaintances on
  any channel.
- professional — work-context emails or messages from coworkers,
  clients, vendors, or work scheduling notes.
- promotional — solicited marketing the recipient opted into (brand
  newsletters, store loyalty offers) that aren't pure noise but also
  aren't transactional.

If you are genuinely uncertain, output classification "personal" with
low confidence — the safer failure mode is to surface a real message
than to drop one.

Return ONLY valid JSON matching this schema:
{
  "classification": "noise" | "transactional" | "personal" | "professional" | "promotional",
  "confidence": <float 0-1>,
  "reasons": [<short strings>]
}

Confidence guidance:
- 0.9+ when the bulk-marketing or transactional structure is unambiguous
- 0.7-0.9 when the signal is clear but content adds some ambiguity
- 0.5-0.7 when weak (default to personal at this range)
- <0.5 always returns classification="personal"

Return the JSON and nothing else.
